Director FR&R Wholesale – Europe & Africa team
Financial Restructuring & Recovery Wholesale & Rural (“FR&R WR”) is responsible for corporate clients in financial distress in the Wholesale and Rural & retail organization. We work in several international teams covering Asia, Australia/New Zealand, South America, North America and Europe & Africa. The Europe & Africa team within FR&R WR is part of the risk management department within the Region Europe & Africa (“FR&R E&A”).
As an Director within FR&R E&A you can make a difference for our Wholesale clients facing financial distress. You will use your expertise and experience for their benefit and thereby you contribute to a healthy credit portfolio and minimise credit losses for Rabobank. Within FR&R, the E&A team is responsible for approximately 100 corporate clients with financial difficulties within the Wholesale organization. Whitin this team we closely look after our clients together with our Business Departments from Core Lending (incl. Corporate Lending, Leveraged Lending and Export Finance). We have the ambition to keep our clients performing and to support them through difficult times in the best possible manner. We take the interests of both our clients as well as Rabobank into account. As (restructuring) partner and expert, FR&R offers specialist assistance to clients in distress with the aim to satisfactorily return these clients back to the Business departments. If the risk becomes too high, FR&R WR uses its expertise and skills to reduce and/or terminate the financing relationship with clients in a respectful manner in order to minimize losses for both the client as well as Rabobank.
You and your job
As Director you are responsible for managing remain/retain and/or exit clients in the region E&A transferred from the commercial/business departments. Additionally, you will deliver advising services to relationship managers and credit officers on early detection of financial difficulties (‘watchlist’), steps to remedy such conditions and share lessons learned in workshops. Ultimately you think and act based on customers’ interest and the underlying premises of the cooperative. Act as reliable partner for business, risk colleagues and internal/external stakeholders. Active stakeholder management is of critical importance to deliver a predictable client journey and effective and efficient decision making.
Management of a designated portfolio of clients in Europe & Africa in financial distress in a diverse product environment including any activities in relation to corporate and financial restructuring and involvement in foreclosing, litigation or liquidation processes;
Maintaining a relationship within syndicate/banking group, financial advisors and external counsels;
Regular reporting on the designated portfolio;
Advisory role on watch list accounts to provide guidance and assistance to relationship managers in developing a strategy to prevent further deterioration;
Foster consistency and best practices in the management and valuation of distressed assets;
Stakeholders management (such as senior product management, relationship managers and credit officers), including providing feedback, relevant support and training;
Comply with laws, rules and regulations, including but not limited to Anti Money Laundering and, where relevant OFAC/Sanctions requirements and the reporting of suspicious activities, as well as all Rabobank policies, procedures and guidelines.
You and your team
Collaboration is at the heart of everything we do. Our FR&R team brings talented people together to manage corporate clients in financial distress. FR&R is worldwide responsible for this FR&R Portfolio and the provisioning policy. FR&R WR is the international division of FR&R and consists of around 90 people worldwide and can be subdivided into the Financial Restructuring teams in the Region (10 countries/13 offices such as the E&A team) and the Overarching Financial Restructuring team in Utrecht. Our E&A team is located in Utrecht.
You and your Talent
Customer focus, analysing & interpreting, supporting & cooperating, internal and external stakeholder management, building and energizing the network are clearly essential for the role of Director FR&R E&A. You have common sense which will help you to apply proper judgement, taking into account all relevant stakeholders and circumstances:
Bachelor or Master degree in financial or target industry;
At least 10 years of experience in account management, risk management or restructuring environment;
Strong track record in strategic thinking and analytical skills;
Knowledge of the Wholesale portfolio, countries, cultures and languages is preferred;
Knowledge of (complex) loan structuring and risk mitigation;
Understanding of credit fundamentals and legal knowledge.
This is what we offer you
Do you want to further develop your knowledge base and professional skills in a dynamic environment? We would love to help you achieve this by focusing firmly on your growth, development, and investing in an environment where you keep learning every day. With us (on the basis of a 36-hour or 40-hour working week), you can also expect:
Up to €8111,77 (scale 11) gross per month;
A thirteenth month and holiday pay;
Travelling to clients and branches in E&A region;
An Employee Benefit Budget 11% of your monthly salary. You decide how to spend this budget. This may include purchasing extra leave days, making extra pension contributions or receiving a monthly cash payment.
This is a selection of the terms of employment for a Director based on a 36-hour working week. This vacancy is for 36 or 40 hours per week. You can find all our terms of employment on https://rabobank.jobs/en/conditions-of-employment.
Application process
We believe in the power of difference. Bringing together people's differences is what makes us an even a better bank. So we are very curious about what you can bring to our team.
We look forward to receive your application for this vacancy in Utrecht.
Applications are open until 5 April 2023. Apply via the “Apply now” button. Responses will be handled in accordance with our vacancy management policy.
If you have any questions about the specific details of this position, please contact Benedikte Richert-Meijer, Head of Financial Restructuring & Recovery Europe & Africa via Benedikte.Richert@rabobank.com.
Lydia van Adrichem, recruiter would be happy to answer any questions about the application procedure via Lydia.van.Adrichem@rabobank.nl.
The application process includes screening / security check. Based on the screening procedures in place at Rabobank, we assess whether new staff are reliable enough to work at Rabobank. Your privacy is important to us. Do you want to know more; Privacy en je persoonsgegevens (rabobank.com)

Junior Quantitative Risk Modeller (IFRS9, Stress Testing, Operational Risk and EC)
At a glance

As a junior quantitative risk analyst, you will play a key role in ensuring that the bank makes informed, data driven decisions. We need skilled junior quantitative risk analysts who have a solid quantitative background and a passion for working with advanced techniques to unlock the valuable information contained within our production and historical data.
Your job

ABN AMRO is a leading Dutch bank, with an international presence across Europe. We need skilled junior quantitative risk analysts who have a solid quantitative background and a passion for working with advanced techniques to unlock the valuable information contained within our production and historical data.
As a junior quantitative risk analyst, you will play a key role in ensuring that the bank makes informed, data driven decisions. You will work with the business to understand the data they generate in their day to day activities. You will decide on the best quantitative methods and techniques to apply to the data sets to unlock the intelligence contained within them. You will work in a team developing new models and methods for quantifying risk, and in evaluating and improving the performance of existing models and methods. Here you can apply your quantitative skills in the real world, on real data sets and business challenges, and make a positive impact for the bank and its customers. You will be supported by your team, which includes experienced risk analysts who can help you to develop and grow your skills.
Working environment

ABN AMRO Risk Modelling is a growing, international team of more than 90 professionals. We are the centre of excellence within the bank for developing quantitative risk models, which inform the bank in its daily decisions, from pricing of deals and granting of customer credits, through to setting and monitoring of market risk limits and determining the capital requirements for the bank.
Your profile

You have a strong quantitative education in an area such as mathematics, econometrics, actuarial studies, or physics. Besides that you have skills in software packages for statistical and data analysis, such as Python, SAS, R, and MatLab. You want to prove yourself in a quantitative modelling environment, and to apply your skills to derive meaningful, robust, data driven models to guide business decisions. You work well within a team, and can take responsibility for making your contribution to successful delivery.
You fit the profile if you meet the following requirements:
Quantitative academic education (Master’s Degree or PhD) in a relevant field, like econometrics, mathematics, actuarial studies or physics;
Good knowledge of statistics, econometrics, financial mathematics;
Able to effectively communicate (in written and spoken English) about your analysis and results;
Experienced in modern programming languages (e.g. Matlab, Python) or statistical languages (e.g. SAS, R);
Strong analytic skills and affinity with data analytics, (pre)processing, and data handling;
Able to work independently and under pressure;
Pro-active attitude and an excellent team player.
The recruitment process includes technical assessmen to test the knowledge of statistics and econometrics. For example, a candidate might be asked how logistic regression works and how to apply it in a given setting. A candidate might also be asked to solve a brain teaser.
We are offering

The opportunity to be the best you can be, work flexible hours and lots of room to grow both personally and professionally;
An informal multi-cultural working environment with great colleagues;
Challenging work on complex and advanced quantitative problems;
The opportunity to pro-actively work on your vitality and fitness;
A competitive salary;
A supplementary benefit budget of 11%, which you can spend on additional fringe benefits;
A personal development budget of EUR 1.000 per year;
An annual public transportation pass or travel budget, depending on the function;
A solid pension plan.
Interested?

We are looking forward to hear from you! Please submit your application online.
Together with your resume and cover letter, please also provide us with your list of grades.
Please only apply to one vacancy; the position that fits best with your experience, skills and knowledge.
Equal opportunities for all

The success of our organisation depends on the quality of our people and the ideas that they have. Truly surprising insights and innovative solutions for our clients result from an interplay of cultures, knowledge and experience. Diversity is therefore extremely important to our organisation. To ensure that everyone at ABN AMRO can develop their talents, we encourage an inclusive culture in which all colleagues feel engaged and appreciated.
